### Variable Declaration and Initialization

The following code demonstrates how to declare and initialize variables with default values in various programming languages.

#### Python
```python
# Declare and initialize variables with default values
name: str = "John Doe"
age: int = 30
is_admin: bool = False

# Print the variables
print(f"Name: {name}")
print(f"Age: {age}")
print(f"Is Admin: {is_admin}")
```

#### Java
```java
public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        // Declare and initialize variables with default values
        String name = "John Doe";
        int age = 30;
        boolean isAdmin = false;

        // Print the variables
        System.out.println("Name: " + name);
        System.out.println("Age: " + age);
        System.out.println("Is Admin: " + isAdmin);
    }
}
```

#### C++
```cpp
#include <iostream>
#include <string>

int main() {
    // Declare and initialize variables with default values
    std::string name = "John Doe";
    int age = 30;
    bool isAdmin = false;

    // Print the variables
    std::cout << "Name: " << name << std::endl;
    std::cout << "Age: " << age << std::endl;
    std::cout << "Is Admin: " << (isAdmin ? "true" : "false") << std::endl;

    return 0;
}
```

#### JavaScript
```javascript
// Declare and initialize variables with default values
let name = "John Doe";
let age = 30;
let isAdmin = false;

// Print the variables
console.log(`Name: ${name}`);
console.log(`Age: ${age}`);
console.log(`Is Admin: ${isAdmin}`);
```

These examples demonstrate how to declare and initialize variables with default values in different programming languages. The variables are then printed to the console to verify their values.
